node.text:
I can't make it any simpler than this, you must fail if you want to succeed.⁣
⁣
By avoiding the risk of failure, by taking the easiest path through life, you're guaranteeing an unfilled existence. ⁣
⁣
You have to take leaps of faith, push towards your goals, take risks, and fail if you wish to succeed.⁣
⁣
Each failure makes you wiser, it allows you to fine-tune your gameplan and it prepares you to overcome future obstacles.⁣
⁣
If you want to succeed, increase your rate of failure.⁣
⁣
This isn't just random advice you hear but never gets practised. You can search for countless examples of successful people who failed many times before they had their success.⁣
⁣
On a personal level, I've been tinkering with ways of making money online since I was a little kid, most failed or had very low results.⁣
⁣
But I learned so much from them that eventually I was able to build a successful online business.⁣
⁣
And it's crazy how many of the skills I learned whilst failing other ways of making money, helped me with my successful business.⁣
⁣
Fail more.⁣
⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣

node.text:
Most people live circular lives, let me prove it...⁣
⁣
How normal does this sound to you?⁣
⁣
January: New goals, new resolutions.⁣
February: Given up on resolutions.⁣
⁣
April/May: Diet/workout for summer.⁣
November: Unhappy with my body again.⁣
⁣
How normal does this sound to you?⁣
⁣
End one relationship, get into another one that ends up with the exact same flaws and issues as your previous one.⁣
⁣
How normal does this to you?⁣
⁣
A friend who tells you about their ideas, goals, dreams. They start for a few days or weeks but then give up. A while later, they're telling you about ideas, goals, dreams again. Repeat.⁣
⁣
Most people revolve, they don't evolve.⁣
⁣
They're dogs chasing after their tail.⁣
⁣
You want to evolve.⁣
⁣
You stick to your resolutions.⁣
⁣
You learn from past mistakes.⁣
⁣
You continually work towards your goals.⁣
⁣
You can continue a project for an extended period of time, always improving it.⁣
⁣
Evolve, don't revolve.⁣
⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣

node.text:
In 2010, psychologist Daniel Kahneman and economist Angus Deaton undertook research to discover if more money meant more happiness, it turns out  beyond a certain point ($75k/year in America), it doesn't...⁣
⁣
Now, of course $75k year is still above average and may seem like a huge sum to those not from a wealthy nation.⁣
⁣
However, it does make it clear that more money is not the answer to increasing happiness.⁣
⁣
More money can bring more comforts, more security and less stress, all amazing things - this is why we pursue more money.⁣
⁣
But, before you think about trying to get more money, you need to get your life in order by making the most of what you already have.⁣
⁣
With a sound mind, a healthy body, clear objectives, good social ties and uplifting hobbies, you can be happy even on a modest income.⁣
⁣
And from that point, any extra money you make can be deployed to make you happier. You just can't make an unhappy person happy with money alone. You can make a happy person even happier with more money though.⁣
⁣
What do you think?⁣
⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣

If you get to the point where you wake up, excited to get through your to do list, you've won at life...⁣
⁣
I consider myself incredibly lucky that I've never had a boss, choose my own hours, can work anywhere and have huge upside potential.⁣
⁣
Of course, some people are just as happy with a good boss and a job they love, in a place they love.⁣
⁣
However, if you're not living that life right now but you want to, you can do it.⁣
⁣
Try different side hustles whilst you continue your stressful job, until you find one you feel passionate about.⁣
⁣
If this also starts to become successful, now you can quit your job.⁣
⁣
I know it's an oversimplification, you'll have to do a lot more research to be able to do it, but I want you to know it is possible.⁣
⁣
I solidly believe that everyone has the capacity to do something they're passionate about.⁣
⁣
And if this starts to happen, jobs nobody enjoys doing will become automated.⁣
⁣
More people will be employed in creative pursuits than factories in this century, mark my words.⁣
⁣
Become one of the pioneers of this shift.⁣
